cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DM, cs.AL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the construction of spanners, which are fundamental graph structures, and presents a new algorithm for constructing a (+6)-spanner with optimal sparsity. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses a distributed implementation of the algorithm in the CONGEST model, which is a model for distributed network algorithms. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper focuses on distributed constructions of spanners. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph structures and their properties. 
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper presents a new algorithm for constructing spanners.
